# Linux Fundamentals

Below are the Linux fundamentals I have encountered and studied so far.

1. Navigation
The filesystem is a tree. You start at / (root).

pwd   --> printing working directory
ls    --> list files in current directory
ls -la  --> list all files with details + hidden files
cd /etc  --> change to /etc directory
cd ..  --> go up one level
cd ~  --> go to your home directory
cd -  --> go back to previous directory
tree /etc  --> show directory tree visually

2. Files
Creating, copying, moving, viewing and searching files

Create & Manage
touch file.txt --> create an empty file
mkdir myfolder --> create a directory
cp file.txt backup.txt --> copy a file
mv file.txt /tmp/ --> move or rename a file
rm file.txt --> delete a file
rm -rf myfolder --> delete folder recursively
